    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-02-06T22:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-02-06T22:34:00-05:00" n="250"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <head>250. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Pakistan</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d250fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_pol1">POL</gloss> 32-1 INDIA-<gloss
                            target="#t_Pak1">PAK</gloss>. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1"
                            >Niact</gloss>; Limit Distribution, Drafted by Gatch; cleared by <gloss
                            target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>, Ludlow, <persName corresp="#p_GJP1"
                            >Grant</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_MGGC1">McGhee</persName>, and <persName
                            corresp="#p_KRW1">Komer</persName>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_CTCJ1">Cameron</persName>. Repeated to New Delhi and
                        London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-02-06T22:34:00-05:00">February 6, 1963, 10:34 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1200. For Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MCWP1">McConaughy</persName>. In
                    addition to delivering President’s message<note n="1" xml:id="d250fn1">See <ref
                            target="#d252">Document 252</ref>.</note> you should make following
                    points to <persName corresp="#p_AKM1">Ayub</persName> regarding the
                    supplementary message he sent to the President by <persName corresp="#p_AA1"
                        >Aziz Ahmed</persName>:<note n="2" xml:id="d250fn2">See <ref target="#d249"
                            >Document 249</ref>.</note>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>As stated explicitly in President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1"
                                >Kennedy</persName>’s letter, we see no possibility of India being
                            willing to give up all of the Vale. Thus we see no utility in idea of
                            arranging transfer of Vale after duration one year or after any period
                            for that matter.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>It is not at all certain that it will be clear within a year whether
                            there is any likelihood at all of recrudescence of fighting between
                            India and China on the Ladakh front. We see no prospect that the <gloss
                                target="#t_Chicom1">Chicom</gloss>s intend, for example, to pull out
                            of Tibet in the foreseeable future. The need for an active defense of
                            Ladakh will be ongoing. [<hi rend="italic">3 lines of source text not
                                declassified</hi>]</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Chinese presence in force at southwestern edge Tibetan Plateau new
                            fact of geopolitical life which must be taken into account by <gloss
                                target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                            >GOI</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>If <persName corresp="#p_AKM1">Ayub</persName> brings up possibility
                            following West New Guinea pattern in Kashmir, you should say that we
                            believe India, unlike the Netherlands, <pb facs="0516" n="490"
                                xml:id="pg_490"/> is unwilling give up possession of what it now
                            holds by such a procedure.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
